{
  "stem": "25598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "But he was caught one day by her, and she nearly killed him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "She was swearing for days.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we knitted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The men worked outside.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father had the misfortune of working at the mass graves.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were hundreds and hundreds of deaths every day from starvation, from typhus, from dysentery, from freezing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some people were shot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some people were beaten to death.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But most people died from the natural causes of typhus, lice, dysentery, hunger, and-- and frost.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a lot of people died on the roads, of course, because they were taking people from one place, moving them to another.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were lucky we stayed in this same place for 3 and 1/2 years.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know how we were so lucky.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maybe my Uncle Armin was in cahoots with the administration.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was stealing from them, and he was getting whatever he was stealing-- ammunition, and salt, and is it called back fat?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That white from pork-- that fat-- meat from pork-- he managed to steal that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was groups of partisans in the forest, and he somehow managed to find a way to transfer that to-- to them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was very important.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he had all kinds of connections.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and maybe that's why we stayed put for 3 and 1/2 years in the same place.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were many days in which we couldn't knit fast enough, or we didn't get wool, or whatever, when there was absolutely no food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and it was a horrible life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You never knew who opens the door, and what they want, and if they're going to shoot you on the spot-- the soldiers-- or-- it was a constant threat to our lives, day and night.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
